perf: Replaced 'react-scroll-parallax' library with static image for the header section
To improve the overall performance of the application, we decided to remove the 'react-scroll-parallax' library and instead use a static image for the header section. This change simplifies the codebase and eliminates the need for additional dependencies. Furthermore, it enhances the user experience by providing a consistent and optimized header rendering across different devices.
